cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.GR

This paper is about monocular depth estimation, which is a computer vision task. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely category. The paper also proposes a novel framework that involves using a stereo matching network to learn depth from synthetic data and using predicted stereo disparity maps to supervise the monocular depth estimation network. This involves machine learning techniques, which suggests that cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also likely categories. The paper also mentions applications in autonomous driving, which suggests that cs.RO (Robotics) is a possible category. Finally, the paper involves using synthetic data generated by graphics engines, which suggests that cs.GR (Graphics) is a possible category.
